<objectXMLWrap>
               <mods xmlns="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3">
                  <recordInfo>
                     <recordOrigin>WorldCat:39964537</recordOrigin>
                     <recordContentSource>ISIL:OCLC-FUG</recordContentSource>
                  </recordInfo>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>University of Florida. Office of the President.</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Administrative policy records, 1928-1947.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>Series P7 contains the administrative records of John James Tigert, third president of the University of Florida. The series contains correspondence, memoranda, building construction records, reports, committee minutes, and other records. Included in the series is Tigert's correspondence with the Association of Land-Grant Colleges and Universities' Executive Committee and the Joint Committee on Accrediting.  Tigert's relationship to the Florida Board of Control is well documented as are the university's academic and administrative units. Of particular note are the extensive files related to military training at the University of Florida during World War II. Also of interest are Tigert's files on the construction of several campus buildings, the development of radio station WRUF, and Tigert's influence on the university's sports programs. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>University of Florida</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>

                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Administrative policy records, 1928.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>Series P6 contains the administrative correspondence of Acting President James M. Farr. Farr served as the University of Florida's vice president from 1905 to 1935. After the death of Albert Alexander Murphree on December 20, 1927, Farr acted as university president until the arrival of James J. Tigert in September 1928. Of special interest is a report on the admission of women, documents related to political attacks on the University by Sidney Catts, and information on the opening of radio station WRUF. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>University of Florida</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>
